The paper discusses the history and recent developments in computer vision and artificial neural networks for image-based recognition, specifically focusing on Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of statistical and structural matchers and artificial neural network-based methods, which fall under the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of GPUs, which falls under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses some open issues regarding DCNNs, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
